# Speech AI Rules

When working with Speech AI tools, follow these guidelines:

## Audio Quality
- Always check audio SNR before scoring â€” below 15dB produces unreliable results
- Recommend WAV format for best accuracy
- Audio must be 0.5s-60s for pronunciation, 0.5s-120s for transcription

## Pronunciation Assessment
- Always include both the audio AND the reference text
- Use `get_phoneme_inventory` to understand which sounds are evaluated
- Present scores with context: 80+ is good, 60-79 acceptable, below 60 needs work
- When confidence is below 0.5, warn the user the result may be unreliable

## Text-to-Speech
- Default voice is `af_heart` (American female, highest quality)
- Speed range: 0.5 to 2.0 (1.0 is normal)
- Max text length: 5000 characters
- Output is base64-encoded WAV (24kHz, 16-bit PCM)

## Privacy
- Audio data is processed in real-time and not stored
- No user data is retained after the API call completes
